tasks.description:
Rewrite the submitted/answered state in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/QuestionPrompt.tsx` to match the ToolCallCard compact single-row pattern: `shadow-msg-tool`, `py-1`, icon + label + value inline on one row, neutral `bg-muted/50` background.

## Current Submitted State (lines 362-399)

The current implementation renders a multi-line layout with `py-2`, status-success background tinting, and header + value on separate lines:

```tsx
<div
  className={cn(
    'my-1 rounded-msg-tool border px-3 py-2 text-sm transition-colors duration-200',
    questionState({ state: 'answered' })
  )}
>
  {hasSpecificAnswers ? (
    <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
      <Check className="mt-0.5 size-(--size-icon-md) shrink-0 text-status-success" />
      <div className="min-w-0 space-y-1.5">
        {questions.map((q, idx) => {
          const displayValue = getDisplayValue(q, idx);
          if (!displayValue) return null;
          return (
            <div key={idx}>
              <span className="text-xs font-semibold">{q.header}</span>
              <p className="text-sm break-words">{displayValue}</p>
            </div>
          );
        })}
      </div>
    </div>
  ) : (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <Check className="size-(--size-icon-md) text-status-success" />
      <span>Questions answered</span>
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

## New Submitted State

Replace the entire submitted state block (the `if (submitted) { ... }` return) with this compact single-row pattern:

```tsx
if (submitted) {
  const hasSpecificAnswers = preAnswers
    ? Object.values(preAnswers).some((v) => v !== '')
    : Object.keys(selections).length > 0;

  // Build a compact summary string
  const summaryParts: string[] = [];
  if (hasSpecificAnswers) {
    if (questions.length === 1) {
      // Single question: show "header: value"
      const displayValue = getDisplayValue(questions[0], 0);
      if (displayValue) {
        summaryParts.push(`${questions[0].header}: ${displayValue}`);
      }
    } else {
      // Multi-question: show "N questions answered"
      summaryParts.push(`${questions.length} questions answered`);
    }
  } else {
    summaryParts.push('Questions answered');
  }

  return (
    <div
      className="bg-muted/50 rounded-msg-tool border px-3 py-1 text-sm shadow-msg-tool transition-all duration-150"
      data-testid="question-prompt-submitted"
    >
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
        <Check className="size-(--size-icon-sm) shrink-0 text-status-success" />
        <span className="truncate">{summaryParts[0]}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Key Changes from Current

1. **Background**: `bg-muted/50` (neutral) instead of `questionState({ state: 'answered' })` which applied `bg-status-success-bg` (green tint). This matches ToolCallCard's neutral `bg-muted/50`.
2. **Shadow**: Added `shadow-msg-tool` to match ToolCallCard.
3. **Padding**: `py-1` instead of `py-2` to match ToolCallCard's compact row.
4. **Transition**: `transition-all duration-150` instead of `transition-colors duration-200` to match ToolCallCard.
5. **Layout**: Single row with icon + text inline. No multi-line header/value. For single-question, shows `header: value`. For multi-question, shows `N questions answered`.
6. **Icon size**: `size-(--size-icon-sm)` instead of `size-(--size-icon-md)` for compact row.
7. **Text truncation**: `truncate` on text for long values.
8. **Removed**: The `questionState({ state: 'answered' })` import usage for the submitted state (it is still used for the pending state, so do NOT remove the import).
9. **Test ID**: Added `data-testid="question-prompt-submitted"` for test targeting.

## TV Variant Update

The `questionState` TV variant in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/ui/message/message-variants.ts` still needs its `answered` state, but it is no longer used by QuestionPrompt's submitted rendering. The `answered` variant can be removed or kept for potential future use. For now, leave it in place but add a comment:

```typescript
export const questionState = tv({
  variants: {
    state: {
      pending: 'border-l-2 border-status-info bg-muted/50',
      // Note: submitted state uses inline neutral classes matching ToolCallCard pattern
      answered: 'border-status-success-border bg-status-success-bg text-status-success-fg',
    },
  },
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- Submitted state renders as a compact single-row: icon + text on one line
- Background is `bg-muted/50` (neutral, no green tint)
- Shadow is `shadow-msg-tool`
- Padding is `py-1` (compact, matching ToolCallCard)
- Transition is `transition-all duration-150`
- Single-question submitted shows `header: value` format
- Multi-question submitted shows `N questions answered`
- Fallback (no specific answers) shows `Questions answered`
- Check icon uses `text-status-success` and `size-(--size-icon-sm)`
- `data-testid="question-prompt-submitted"` is present
- TypeScript compilation succeeds

Update `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/QuestionPrompt.test.tsx` to account for the new compact single-row submitted state rendering.

## Test Changes Required

### 1. Update 'collapses to compact summary after successful submission' test (around line 308)

The current test checks for status-success styling and the header text 'Approach' as a separate element. The new compact format renders `header: value` as a single string on one row.

**Current:**
```typescript
it('collapses to compact summary after successful submission (shows status-success styling)', async () => {
  render(<QuestionPrompt {...baseProps} questions={[singleSelectQuestion]} />);
  const radio = screen.getAllByRole('radio')[0];
  fireEvent.click(radio);
  fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /submit/i }));

  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.queryByRole('radio')).toBeNull();
    expect(screen.getByText('Approach')).toBeDefined();
    expect(screen.getByText('Reschedule the internal meeting')).toBeDefined();
  });

  const container = screen.getByText('Approach').closest('div[class*="status-success"]');
  expect(container).not.toBeNull();
});
```

**New:**
```typescript
it('collapses to compact single-row summary after successful submission', async () => {
  render(<QuestionPrompt {...baseProps} questions={[singleSelectQuestion]} />);
  const radio = screen.getAllByRole('radio')[0];
  fireEvent.click(radio);
  fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /submit/i }));

  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.queryByRole('radio')).toBeNull();
    // Single-question submitted shows "header: value" format
    expect(screen.getByText('Approach: Reschedule the internal meeting')).toBeDefined();
  });

  // Container uses neutral bg-muted/50 with shadow-msg-tool (ToolCallCard pattern)
  const container = screen.getByTestId('question-prompt-submitted');
  expect(container).not.toBeNull();
  expect(container.className).toContain('shadow-msg-tool');
  expect(container.className).toContain('bg-muted/50');
});
```

