Update `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/ToolApproval.test.tsx` to account for the new compact single-row decided state rendering (with status icons and badge pills) and the Button component usage in pending state.

## Test Changes Required

### 1. Update 'shows "Approved" after approve' test (around line 105)

The "Approved" text now renders inside a badge `<span>` with status styling. The `screen.getByText('Approved')` query should still work since RTL matches visible text content regardless of wrapper element. However, add assertions for the new icon and badge styling.

**Current:**
```typescript
it('shows "Approved" after approve', async () => {
  const ref = createRef<ToolApprovalHandle>();
  render(<ToolApproval {...baseProps} ref={ref} />);
  ref.current!.approve();
  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText('Approved')).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```

**New:**
```typescript
it('shows "Approved" with check icon and badge after approve', async () => {
  const ref = createRef<ToolApprovalHandle>();
  render(<ToolApproval {...baseProps} ref={ref} />);
  ref.current!.approve();
  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText('Approved')).toBeDefined();
    // Check icon should be present with success color
    const container = screen.getByTestId('tool-approval-decided');
    const svg = container.querySelector('svg');
    expect(svg).not.toBeNull();
    expect(svg!.classList.toString()).toContain('text-status-success');
    // Container should have neutral background with shadow
    expect(container.className).toContain('bg-muted/50');
    expect(container.className).toContain('shadow-msg-tool');
  });
});
```

