### 5. Verify existing pending state tests still pass

The pending state button tests query by `screen.getByRole('button', { name: /approve/i })` and `screen.getByRole('button', { name: /deny/i })`. The `Button` component renders as `<button>` with the same text content, so these queries should continue working. The Kbd hints tests also look for `<kbd>` elements, which are rendered inside the Button just as before.

No changes needed for:
- 'renders tool name and approve/deny buttons'
- 'renders tool arguments display'
- 'isActive prop' describe block (ring-2, Kbd hints)
- 'imperative handle' tests for approve/deny transport calls
- 'guards against action after decided'
- 'countdown timer' describe block

### 6. Verify the 'transitions to denied state when timeout expires' test

This test checks for `screen.getByText(/Auto-denied/)` and `data-decision="denied"` — both still work with the new layout since the auto-denied message is preserved below the compact row. No changes needed.

